y_count-carnivore|title=Body Count Carnivore|last=Smith-Engelhardt|first=Joe|date=March 5, 2020|website=[[Exclaim!]]|language=en-ca|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Kerrang!]]''\n| rev3score = 3/5<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kerrang.com/reviews/album-review-body-count-carnivore/|title=Album Review: Body Count \u2013 Carnivore|last=Law|first=Sam|date=March 6, 2020|website=[[Kerrang!]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Louder Sound]]''\n| rev4score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.loudersound.com/reviews/body-counts-carnivore-raucous-riffage-ferocious-rants-and-amy-lee|title=Body Count's Carnivore: raucous riffage, ferocious rants and... Amy Lee?|last=Lawson|first=Dom|date=March 6, 2020|website=[[Metal Hammer]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev5       = ''[[Metal Storm (webzine)|Metal Storm]]''\n| rev5Score  = (7.5/10)<ref name=\"Metal Storm\">{{cite web |title= Body Count - Carnivore review |url=http://metalstorm.net/pub/review.php?review_id=15481 |publisher=Metal Storm |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Carnivore''''' is the seventh studio album by American [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]] band [[Body Count (band)|Body Count]], released on March 6, 2020, by [[Century Media Records|Century Media]]. The singles \"Carnivore\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://loudwire.com/body-count-carnivore-song/|title=Body Count Dish Out Brutal New Song 'Carnivore'|last=DiVita|first=Joe|website=[[Loudwire]]|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref> and \"Bum-Rush\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://loudwire.com/body-count-bum-rush-video/|title=Body Count Start a Revolution With 'Bum-Rush' Video|last=Childers|first=Chad|website=Loudwire|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref> were released to promote the album.\n\n== Background ==\nExplaining the title, vocalist [[Ice-T]] reported to ''[[Loudwire]]'' in 2018, prior to the album's recording:<blockquote>\"It's basically: 'Fuck vegans.' We figure, anything carnivorous pretty much kicks ass. We're carnivorous! I'm not [really] saying 'Fuck vegans.' Everyone's so pussy right now, [so] we're carnivores.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theprp.com/2018/05/20/news/body-count-have-plans-to-work-on-their-new-album-carnivore/|title=Body Count Have Plans To Work On Their New Album \"Carnivore\"|date=2018-05-20|website=Theprp.com|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref></blockquote>\nThe album art was created by Zbigniew M. Bielak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/listen-to-title-track-of-new-body-count-album-carnivore/|title=Listen To Title Track Of New BODY COUNT Album, 'Carnivore'|date=December 13, 2019|website=[[Blabbermouth.net]]}}</ref> It is the first album to not feature any songwriting credits for [[Ernie C]].\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Standard edition\n| all_writing = [[Ice-T|Tracy Marrow]], Vincent Dennis, Will Dorsey and [[Will Putney]] except where stated\n| total_length = 35:55\n\n| title1   = Carnivore\n| length1  = 3:12\n\n| title2   = Point the Finger\n| note2    = featuring [[Power Trip (band)|Riley Gale]]\n| writer2  = [[Ice-T|Tracy Marrow]], Vincent Dennis, Will Dorsey, Riley Gale, Will Putney\n| length2  = 2:39\n\n| title3   = Bum-Rush\n| length3  = 3:24\n\n| title4   = [[Ace of Spades (song)|Ace of Spades]]\n| note4    = [[Mot\u00f6rhead]] cover\n| writer4  = [[Eddie Clarke (musician)|Eddie Clarke]], [[Lemmy|Ian Kilmister]], [[Phil \"Philthy Animal\" Taylor|Phil Taylor]]\n| length4  = 3:00\n\n| title5   = Another Level\n| note5    = featuring [[Jamey Jasta]]\n| writer5  = Marrow, [[Jamey Jasta]]\n| length5  = 4:12\n\n| title6   = [[Colors (Ice-T song)|Colors - 2020]]\n| writer6  = Marrow, [[Afrika Islam|Charles Andre Glenn]]\n| length6  = 4:26\n\n| title7   = No Remorse\n| length7  = 3:13\n\n| title8   = When I'm Gone\n| note8    = featuring [[Amy Lee]]\n| writer8  = Marrow, Dennis, Dorsey, [[Amy Lee]], Putney\n| length8  = 4:36\n\n| title9   = Thee Critical Breakdown\n| length9  = 3:12\n\n| title10  = The Hate Is Real\n| length10 = 4:01\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Deluxe edition (Disc 1)\n\n| title11  = [[6 in the Mornin'|6 in tha Morning - 2020]]\n| note11   = Unreleased demo\n| writer11 = Marrow, [[The Unknown DJ|Andre Pierre]]\n| length11 = 3:31\n\n| title12   = No Lives Matter\n| note12    = Live in Australia 2017\n| length12  = 4:57\n\n| title13   = Black Hoodie\n| note13    = Live in Australia 2017\n| writer13  = [[Ernie C|Ernie Cunnigan]], [[Juan Garcia (guitarist)|Juan Garcia]], Marrow, Dennis, Putney\n| length13  = 3:26\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Deluxe edition (Disc 2)\n\n| total_length = \n| title1   = Carnivore\n| note1   = instrumental\n| length1  = 3:12\n\n| title2   = Point the Finger\n| note2   = instrumental\n| length2  = 2:39\n\n| title3   = Bum-Rush\n| note3   = instrumental\n| length3  = 3:24\n\n| title4   = Another Level\n| note4   = instrumental\n| length4  = 4:12\n\n| title5   = Colors - 2020\n| note5   = instrumental\n| length5  = 4:26\n\n| title6   = No Remorse\n| note6   = instrumental\n| length6  = 3:13\n\n| title7   = When I'm Gone\n| note7   = instrumental\n| length7  = 4:12\n\n| title8   = Thee Critical Breakdown\n| note8   = instrumental\n| length8  = 3:12\n\n| title9  = The Hate Is Real\n| note9   = instrumental\n| length9 = 3:54\n\n| title10  = 6 in tha Morning - 2020\n| note10   = instrumental\n| length10 = 3:24\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Body Count\n*[[Ice-T]] \u2013 lead vocals\n*[[Ernie C]] \u2013 lead guitar\n*[[Juan Garcia (guitarist)|Juan of the Dead]] \u2013 rhythm guitar\n*Vincent Price \u2013 bass, additional voices on \"The Hate Is Real\"\n*Ill Will \u2013 drums\n*Sean E Sean \u2013 sampler, backing vocals\n*Little Ice \u2013 hype man, backing vocals\n{{col-2}}\n;Other personnel\n*[[Will Putney]] \u2013 production, mixing, mastering, additional guitar\n*Ri