{"title_page": "Zaur Ramazanov", "text_new": "{{short description|Azerbaijani footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Zaur Ramazanov\n| image       = \n| caption     = \n| fullname    = Zaur Ramazanov\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1976|7|27}}\n| birth_place = [[Azerbaijan SSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| position    = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| years1 = 2002\u20132003\n| years2 = 2003\u20132004\n| years3 = 2004\u20132005\n| years4 = 2005\u20132008\n| years5 = 2008\u20132009\n| years6 = 2009\u20132010\n| years7 = 2010\u20132011\n| years8 = 2010\n| caps1  = ?\n| caps2  = 20\n| caps3  = 26\n| caps4  = 69\n| caps5  = 24\n| caps6  = 0\n| caps7  = 7\n| caps8  = 0\n| goals1 = ?\n| goals2 = 14\n| goals3 = 21\n| goals4 = 33\n| goals5 = 4\n| goals6 = 0\n| goals7 = 0\n| goals8 = 0\n| clubs1 = [[MOIK Baku]]\n| clubs2 = [[Bak\u0131l\u0131 PFK|Bakili Baku]]\n| clubs3 = [[Karvan FK|Karvan]]\n| clubs4 = [[Khazar Lankaran FK|Khazar Lankaran]]\n| clubs5 = [[Qaraba\u011f FK|Qaraba\u011f]]\n| clubs6 = [[FC Baku|Baku]]\n| clubs7 = [[Karvan FK|Karvan]]\n| clubs8 = [[Khazar Lankaran FK|Khazar Lankaran]]\n| nationalyears1 = 2003\u20132008\n| nationalteam1  = [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 14\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n|pcupdate = 16 December 2019\n|ntupdate = 16 December 2019\n}}\n\n'''Zaur Ramazanov''' (born 27 July 1976) is a retired [[Azerbaijan]]i international [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who played as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]]. \n\n==Career==\n===Club===\nRamazanov was top scorer in [[Azerbaijan Premier League]] season 2004&ndash;05, 2006\u201307. \n\n===International===\nRamazanov made 14 appearances for the [[Azerbaijan national football team]].<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|author=Mamrud, Roberto|title=Azerbaijan - Record International Players|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/azer-recintlp.html|date=2009-07-16|accessdate=2009-09-11}}</ref><ref name=\"NFT Stats\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nZaur is the elder brother of fellow [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]] international footballer [[Aghabala Ramazanov|Aghabala]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0420\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0438\u043b \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0432 \u0428\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0444 |url=http://www.azerifootball.com/ru/13/news/44495.html |website=azerifootball.com/ |publisher=Azeri Football |accessdate=16 December 2019 |language=Russian |date=16 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!colspan=3|[[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2003||2||0\n|-\n|2004||3||1\n|-\n|2005||3||0\n|-\n|2006||0||0\n|-\n|2007||2||0\n|-\n|2008||4||0\n|-\n!Total||14||0\n|}\n''Statistics accurate as of match played 4 June 2008''<ref name=\"NFT Stats\">{{cite web |url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/9651/Zaur_Ramazanov.html |title=Zaur Ramazanov |website=National-Football-Teams.com |access-date=16 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''[[FK Khazar Lankaran|Khazar Lankaran]]'''\n*[[Azerbaijan Premier League]] (1): [[2006\u201307 Azerbaijan Top League|2006/07]]\n*[[Azerbaijan Cup]] (2): 2006\u201307, [[2007\u201308 Azerbaijan Cup|2007/08]]\n*[[Commonwealth of Independent States Cup|CIS Cup]] (1): [[2008 Commonwealth of Independent States Cup|2008]]\n\n===Individual===\n<!--LEAGUE AND FEDERATION-SANCTIONED AWARDS ONLY. No fan or magazine-voted awards. Listed in chronological order from last time won.-->\n*[[Azerbaijan Premier League]] Top Scorer (2): 2004-05, 2006\u201307\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110715134508/http://www.qarabagh.com/site/?name=viewpers&pid=185&cat=3&lang=1 Player profile at qarabagh.com]\n*{{NFT player|pid=9651}}\n\n{{Azerbaijan Premier League top scorers}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2011}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ramazanov, Zaur}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani footballers]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijan international footballers]]\n[[Category:Qaraba\u011f FK players]]\n[[Category:Khazar Lankaran FK players]]\n[[Category:MOIK Baku players]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijan Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Baku]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n{{Azerbaijan-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Zaur Ramazanov\n| image       = \n| caption     = \n| fullname    = Zaur Ramazanov\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1976|7|27}}\n| birth_place = [[Azerbaijan SSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| position    = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| years1 = 2002\u20132003\n| years2 = 2003\u20132004\n| years3 = 2004\u20132005\n| years4 = 2005\u20132008\n| years5 = 2008\u20132009\n| years6 = 2009\u20132010\n| years7 = 2010\u20132011\n| years8 = 2010\n| caps1  = ?\n| caps2  = 20\n| caps3  = 26\n| caps4  = 69\n| caps5  = 24\n| caps6  = 0\n| caps7  = 7\n| caps8  = 0\n| goals1 = ?\n| goals2 = 14\n| goals3 = 21\n| goals4 = 33\n| goals5 = 4\n| goals6 = 0\n| goals7 = 0\n| goals8 = 0\n| clubs1 = [[MOIK Baku]]\n| clubs2 = [[Bak\u0131l\u0131 PFK|Bakili Baku]]\n| clubs3 = [[Karvan FK|Karvan]]\n| clubs4 = [[Khazar Lankaran FK|Khazar Lankaran]]\n| clubs5 = [[Qaraba\u011f FK|Qaraba\u011f]]\n| clubs6 = [[FC Baku|Baku]]\n| clubs7 = [[Karvan FK|Karvan]]\n| clubs8 = [[Khazar Lankaran FK|Khazar Lankaran]]\n| nationalyears1 = 2003\u20132008\n| nationalteam1  = [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 14\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n|pcupdate = 16 December 2019\n|ntupdate = 16 December 2019\n}}\n\n'''Zaur Ramazanov''' (born 27 July 1976) is a retired [[Azerbaijan]]i international [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who played as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]]. \n\n==Career==\n===Club===\nRamazanov was top scorer in [[Azerbaijan Premier League]] season 2004&ndash;05, 2006\u201307. \n\n===International===\nRamazanov made 14 appearances for the [[Azerbaijan national football team]].<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|author=Mamrud, Roberto|title=Azerbaijan - Record International Players|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/azer-recintlp.html|date=2009-07-16|accessdate=2009-09-11}}</ref><ref name=\"NFT Stats\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nZaur is the elder brother of fellow [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]] international footballer [[Aghabala Ramazanov|Aghabala]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0420\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0438\u043b \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0432 \u0428\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0444 |url=http://www.azerifootball.com/ru/13/news/44495.html |website=azerifootball.com/ |publisher=Azeri Football |accessdate=16 December 2019 |language=Russian |date=16 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!colspan=3|[[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2003||2||0\n|-\n|2004||3||1\n|-\n|2005||3||0\n|-\n|2006||0||0\n|-\n|2007||2||0\n|-\n|2008||4||0\n|-\n!Total||14||0\n|}\n''Statistics accurate as of match played 4 June 2008''<ref name=\"NFT Stats\">{{cite web |url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/9651/Zaur_Ramazanov.html |title=Zaur Ramazanov |website=National-Football-Teams.com |access-date=16 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''[[FK Khazar Lankaran|Khazar Lankaran]]'''\n*[[Azerbaijan Premier League]] (1): [[2006\u201307 Azerbaijan Top League|2006/07]]\n*[[Azerbaijan Cup]] (2): 2006\u201307, [[2007\u201308 Azerbaijan Cup|2007/08]]\n*[[Commonwealth of Independent States Cup|CIS Cup]] (1): [[2008 Commonwealth of Independent States Cup|2008]]\n\n===Individual===\n<!--LEAGUE AND FEDERATION-SANCTIONED AWARDS ONLY. 