 nominations in the two 'actor' categories, it could have only won 13 awards). At 11 wins, it failed to beat the record of 12 held by ''[[The Producers (musical)|The Producers]]''.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5%;\" | Year\n! style=\"width:20%;\" | Award\n! style=\"width:40%;\" | Category\n! style=\"width:25%;\" | Nominee\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"27\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2016\n| rowspan=\"16\" | [[70th Tony Awards|Tony Awards]]<ref>Viagas, Robert. [http://www.playbill.com/article/tony-time-its-broadways-biggest-night \" ''Hamilton'' Tops Tony Awards With 11 Wins\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170130021429/http://www.playbill.com/article/tony-time-its-broadways-biggest-night |date=January 30, 2017 }}, Playbill, June 12, 2016</ref>\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[Tony Award for Best Musical|Best Musical]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Tony Award for Best Book of a Musical|Best Book of a Musical]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Lin-Manuel Miranda]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Tony Award for Best Original Score|Best Original Score]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Tony Award for Best Actor in a Musical|Best Actor in a Musical]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Leslie Odom Jr.]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Musical|Best Actress in a Musical]]\n| [[Phillipa Soo]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Tony Award for Best Featured Actor in a Musical|Best Featured Actor in a Musical]]\n| [[Daveed Diggs]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Jonathan Groff]]\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Christopher Jackson (actor)|Christopher Jackson]]\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Tony Award for Best Featured Actress in a Musical|Best Featured Actress in a Musical]]\n| [[Ren\u00e9e Elise Goldsberry]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Tony Award for Best Scenic Design of a Musical|Best Scenic Design of a Musical]]\n| David Korins\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Tony Award for Best Costume Design of a Musical|Best Costume Design of a Musical]]\n| [[Paul Tazewell]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Tony Award for